  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sensitivity/vad-hemolysis-sa-001",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global Sensitivity Analysis — VAD Hemolysis CFD Model Inputs",
    "description": "Variance-based Sobol sensitivity analysis (n=4000 quasi-random samples, Saltelli sampling scheme) was performed varying six model inputs: volumetric flow rate (1-7 L/min), rotational speed (2000-5000 RPM), inlet hematocrit (35-45%), hemolysis model coefficient alpha (0.62-0.78), hemolysis model exponent beta (0.765-0.835), and blood viscosity (0.003-0.005 Pa·s). The hemolysis coefficient alpha is the dominant first-order index (S1=0.54) for NIH predictions, followed by flow rate (S1=0.23). Total-order indices confirm negligible higher-order interactions (ST-S1 < 0.05 for all inputs), supporting the adequacy of independent uncertainty propagation in the Monte Carlo UQ."
  },
